channel.title: Blueprint Lookup?
channel.description:
Hey, Does anyone know where I can get the blueprints for a specific location. Me and my friends got a great new hangout, but we think there's someone going in it. It's a country club that's been closed for almost a year. Anyways, we want to plant some traps, and get to know the place better, so I thought, what's better than having a blueprint. The address is:
4003 Palm Tree Blvd Cape Coral, FL 33904-8436 United States
A website that gives them, or something of the sort would be greatly appreciated. Thanks. Buzzy

item.title: Blueprint Lookup?
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

Be careful giving out adresses over the internet. Your taking a major risk by doing that.

Anyways I doubt there is a site to lookup blueprint plans, I mean who would upload them all in the first place. Private buildings probably don’t just hand them out like that.

You could try going to city hall to find out more information. Where I live you can get blue prints for any public building in my town. As far as I know they don’t hand out any blue prints for a private owned building though. Maybe even your library could have something though.

Also you could try making your own blueprints if you have free acess all around the building.
